[{"id":31221,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["Methylamine","Ammonia","Formaldehyde","N-Methyl urea"],"answer":2,"solution":"Polymer given here is Urea-formaldehyde resin and monomer of this compounds are urea and formaldehyde.<br /><img height=\"197\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/58c25c12-bd93-4d58-9e41-8a5124f334b6-image.png\" width=\"786\" /><br /><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/265dd0e0-d880-4f85-87cd-06298e27c123-image.png\" style=\"width: 914px; height: 233px;\" />","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (09 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":31199,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["Glyptal","PHBV","Novolac","Dacron"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p>Polyester&nbsp;is any of a group of polymers that consist basically the&nbsp;repeated units of an ester. Polyester is a synthetic fabric that&rsquo;s usually derived from petroleum. Dacron, PHBV and Glyptal are polyesters. Novolac is a linear condensation polymer of phenol and formaldehyde.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (31 Aug Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":31190,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["A Both Assertion and Reason are true and&nbsp;Reason is the correct explanation of Assertion","Both Assertion and&nbsp;Reason are true but Reason is not the correct explanation of Assertion.","Assertion is true but&nbsp;Reason is false.","Assertion is false but Reason is true."],"answer":2,"solution":"<p><strong>Natural rubber</strong></p><p>Natural rubber is a polymer of isoprene, and obtained from natural source-latex tree. In natural rubber, isoprene units are joined together in head-to-tail fashion and all double bonds in the polymer chain have cis configurations as shown in the given figure.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/2bd93ed4-0ea0-497f-b8b7-f06206945602-image.png\" style=\"width: 650px; height: 181px;\" /></p><p>The polymer contains cis repeating units and has a molecular weight ranging from <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>100</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>000</mn></math> upto&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>000</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>000</mn></math></p><p>The cis arrangement of the double bonds in natural rubber prevents the rubber molecules from fitting into an ordered structure. Thus, rubber is an amorphous polymer. Because of the random coiling of its polymer chains, rubber stretches easily. When stretched, the rubber molecules are forced into a higher energy state. when the tension is released, rubber snaps back to its original random coiled state but it is nonpolar therefore statement-II is incorrect.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (28 Jun Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":31175,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi>IV</mi><mo>;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi><mo>;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi>II</mi><mo>;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi>II</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi>II</mi><mo>;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi>III</mi><mo>;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi><mo>;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi>IV</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi>IV</mi><mo>;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi>III</mi><mo>;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi><mo>;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi>II</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi>II</mi><mo>;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi><mo>;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi>IV</mi><mo>;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi>III</mi></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Thermoset plastics retain their form and stay solid under heat once cured.&nbsp;Urea-formaldehyde is an example of thermosetting polymer.&nbsp;Polymers which disintegrate by themselves over a period of time due to environmental degradation by bacteria etc. are called biodegradable polymers. Nylon-2-nylon-6 is an example of&nbsp;biodegradable polymer.&nbsp;Any artificial elastomer is referred to as synthetic rubber. Buna-N is an example of synthetic rubber.&nbsp;Polyester is a synthetic or man-made fiber material. Dacron is an example polyester.</p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (10 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":31189,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["Nylon-&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>6</mn></math>","Buna-<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></math>","Terylene","Bakelite"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p>Synthetic rubber is any vulcanisable rubber like polymer, which is capable of getting stretched to twice its length. However, it returns to its original shape and size as soon as the external stretching force is released. Thus, synthetic rubbers are either homopolymers of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>3</mn></math> - butadiene derivatives or copolymers of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>3</mn></math> - butadiene or its derivatives with another unsaturated monomer.</p><p>Buna-N&nbsp;is an example of synthetic rubber.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (29 Jun Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":31228,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/dffe9c7a-b485-4885-a447-763b4f0eb437-image.png\" style=\"width: 278px; height: 138px;\" /></p>","<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/0e00bccc-9d9a-47ad-acfb-0d0d7fb4199b-image.png\" style=\"width: 236px; height: 184px;\" /></p>","<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/4d458400-cd58-42ad-bc84-271375d5c4be-image.png\" style=\"width: 270px; height: 176px;\" /></p>","<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/83a978e6-55c8-43ed-ae38-40fd637e64bb-image.png\" style=\"width: 262px; height: 152px;\" /></p>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p>Free Radical Polymeristation<br /><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/7a8b7426-389c-4a16-be1b-bc81ae761a3b-image.png\" style=\"width: 568px; height: 265px;\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (09 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":31259,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["polyester polymer","polyamide polymer","polyethylene polymer","polyvinyl polymer"],"answer":1,"solution":"Nylon is a polyamide polyer","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2003","image":null},{"id":31227,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["<p><img height=\"136\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/37d10d93-285f-4701-92b5-d17b364dd877-image.png\" width=\"252\" /></p>","<p><img height=\"182\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/36d27e09-4002-40be-9c7d-168a00238858-image.png\" width=\"217\" /></p>","<p><img height=\"201\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/f63bcdfb-9b73-4920-991c-df321f44cc6b-image.png\" width=\"241\" /></p>","<p><img height=\"147\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/a67938a5-31f5-4093-9bd6-7ccd609e090b-image.png\" width=\"273\" /></p>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p><img height=\"369\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/25ca80b3-a520-4845-85f2-c83f642a303a-image.png\" width=\"586\" /></p><p>&nbsp;</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (10 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":31195,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/14e0caf6-38e6-419d-b887-d00544f47dc7-dc434a5f-ba26-4af6-9109-a8bc3a0579a2-88fe126a-65b7-4bab-b7ed-4b97efd0cf14-image.png\" style=\"width: 785px; height: 171px;\" />&nbsp; &nbsp; The molar mass of the monomer unit in the box&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>107</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"></math>Assume there are&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mo>&#160;</mo></math>number of monomer units,</p><p>So, total molar mass&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>107</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>963</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>9</mn></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (25 Jun Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":31194,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp;and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp;are correct","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp;and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp;are correct","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">E</mi></mfenced></math> are correct","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp;and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp;are correct"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Which of the following set are correct regarding polymer.</p><p>Buna <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi></math>&nbsp;is copolymer of butadiene <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>+</mo></math>&nbsp;styrene</p><p>Nylon <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>6</mn></math>&nbsp;is condensation polymer of adipic Acid and hexanediamine.</p><p>Nylon <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>6</mn></math>&nbsp;is fibre.</p><p>Terylene is fibre&nbsp;not thermosetting polymer</p><p>Buna-<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></math> is copolymer not&nbsp;Homopolymer</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (26 Jun Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":31255,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/MLDW-OJqWV3OzkVuWNfHyhfFyFsw2Egz6WKU2z_ZVGY.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/gIYj1e-GQ3IcaKbPb7-SJLnChjJG0nWGFPDiG7aAGgA.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/wnRFGrlM3YkZzwhTJa7mcRfd9Y7nBJF8StSyjCukZdI.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/0zAhOTSr2zu1X_M3qpXJDsXq8u4xWktSxFq7SN4fXlc.original.fullsize.png\"><br>"],"answer":2,"solution":"No Solution Available","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2009","image":null},{"id":31247,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["polypropylene","polyvinyl chloride","polythene","polymethyl methacrylate"],"answer":3,"solution":"Polymethyl methacrylate is hard, fairly rigid. It is used for optical lenses.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2013 (22 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":31174,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/bdf5b549-64c8-4485-b42d-77b706192149.png\" style=\"width: 450px; height: 102px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/5b12677b-b78e-466b-8747-c552ef10b103.png\" style=\"width: 450px; height: 94px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/25c856e7-381c-4d58-bdd8-3d444d442837.png\" style=\"width: 350px; height: 78px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/cea6046c-d887-4ff0-aff4-65649bd9b74a.png\" style=\"width: 350px; height: 78px;\" />"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p>Buna-S is a copolymer of 1,3-butadiene and styrene. It is prepared by copolymerisation of 1,3 butadiene and styrene along with sodium.&nbsp;In this process peroxide is used as a catalyst at&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mn>5</mn><mo>&#8728;</mo></msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math>&nbsp;therefore the formed product is also known as cold rubber.&nbsp;</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/68f0e126-7a1e-49dc-91db-a4388494dd78-1ed3be76-2287-49b9-a553-40cd925c96d5-image.png\" style=\"width: 626px; height: 130px;\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (10 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":31203,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["Novolac","Buna-N","Acrilan","Neoprene"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>Phenol</mtext><mo>+</mo><mi>HCHO</mi><mover><mo>&#8594;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></mover><mtext>Novolac&#160;(Given&#160;structure)</mtext><mover><mo>&#8594;</mo><mtext>Polymerisation</mtext></mover><mtext>Bakelite(Cross&#160;linked&#160;polymer)</mtext></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (25 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":31223,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>HOOH</mi><msub><mfenced separators=\"|\"><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfenced><mn>4</mn></msub><mi>COOH</mi><mo>,</mo><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><msub><mfenced separators=\"|\"><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfenced><mn>4</mn></msub><msub><mi>NH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>HOOC</mi><msub><mfenced separators=\"|\"><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfenced><mn>4</mn></msub><mi>COOH</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><msub><mfenced separators=\"|\"><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfenced><mn>6</mn></msub><msub><mi>NH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>HOOC</mi><msub><mfenced separators=\"|\"><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfenced><mn>6</mn></msub><mi>COOH</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><msub><mfenced separators=\"|\"><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfenced><mn>4</mn></msub><msub><mi>NH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>HOOC</mi><msub><mfenced separators=\"|\"><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfenced><mn>6</mn></msub><mi>COOH</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><msub><mfenced separators=\"|\"><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfenced><mn>6</mn></msub><msub><mi>NH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p>Nylon<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>6</mn></math> is made up of hexamethylenediamine <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><msub><mfenced separators=\"|\"><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfenced><mn>6</mn></msub><msub><mi>NH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow></mfenced></math> and&nbsp;adipic acid <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>HCOO</mi><mo>-</mo><msub><mfenced separators=\"|\"><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfenced><mn>4</mn></msub><mo>-</mo><mi>COOH</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>.</mo></math><br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>NH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mfenced separators=\"|\"><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfenced><mn>6</mn></msub><msub><mi>NH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><mi>HCOO</mi><msub><mfenced separators=\"|\"><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfenced><mn>4</mn></msub><mi>COOH</mi></math><br /><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/df846fff-7d15-45c3-87b4-2c794e8e557d-image.png\" style=\"width: 504px; height: 148px;\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (12 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":31253,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["$\\mathrm{LiAlH}_4$","$\\mathrm{HNO}_3$","$\\mathrm{AlCl}_3$","$\\mathrm{BuLi}$"],"answer":2,"solution":"Lewis acids can initiate the cationic polymerization.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2012 (Offline)","image":null},{"id":31205,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["PHBV","Buna-S","Novolac","Dacron"],"answer":2,"solution":"Novolac (phenol formaldehyde Resin) + Formaldehyde&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8594;</mo></math> Bakelite","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (20 Jul Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":31176,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["<p>Polyethene</p>","<p>Polycarbonate</p>","<p>Polyamide</p>","<p>Polyacrylonitrile</p>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<blockquote><p>The addition polymerisation of acrylonitrile in presence of a peroxide catalyst leads to the formation of polyacrylonitrile. The commercial name of polyacrylonitrile is orlon (acrilan). That is, it is used as a substitute for wool in making commercial fibres as orlon or acrilan.&nbsp;</p><p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/ffff4193-687e-4fa5-9b67-ac8c70595f55.png\" style=\"width: 454px; height: 99px;\" /></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (06 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":31172,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["<strong>Statement I&nbsp;</strong>is<strong> </strong>false<strong>&nbsp;</strong>but<strong>&nbsp;Statement II&nbsp;</strong>is true","<strong>Statement I&nbsp;</strong>is<strong>&nbsp;</strong>true<strong>&nbsp;</strong>but<strong>&nbsp;Statement II&nbsp;</strong>is false","Both&nbsp;<strong>Statement I </strong>and<strong>&nbsp;Statement II </strong>are true","Both&nbsp;<strong>Statement I </strong>and<strong>&nbsp;Statement II </strong>are false"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Low Density Polyethylene&nbsp;is obtained by the polymerisation of ethene under high pressure of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1000</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>2000</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>atm</mi></math> at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>350</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>570</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi></math> in the presence of an initiator. High Density Polyethylene&nbsp;is obtained when polymerisation is done in the presence of Ziegler-Natta catalyst at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>333</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>343</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi></math> under <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>atm</mi></math> pressure.&nbsp;Nylon-6 is manufactured from the monomer called caprolactam. The monomer caprolactam is heated at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>533</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>543</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi></math>in an inert atmosphere, it polymerises to give nylon-6.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (11 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":31249,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["Acetaldehyde","Chlorobenzene","Formaldehyde","Acetamide"],"answer":2,"solution":"Phenol and formaldehyde undergo condensation polymerisation under two different conditions to give a cross linked polymer called bakelite.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2012 (26 May Online)","image":null},{"id":31204,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["(a) - (iii), (b)-(iv), (c) -(ii), (d) -(i)","(a) - (ii), (b)-(iii), (c)-(iv), (d) -(i)","(a) - (ii), (b)-(i), (c) -(iv), (d) -(iii)","(a) - (iii), (b)-(i), (c) -(iv), (d) -(ii)"],"answer":1,"solution":"<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" style=\"width: 500px;\">\t<tbody>\t\t<tr>\t\t\t<td>&nbsp;</td>\t\t\t<td>List - I</td>\t\t\t<td>&nbsp;</td>\t\t\t<td>List - II</td>\t\t</tr>\t\t<tr>\t\t\t<td>(a)</td>\t\t\t<td>Chloroprene</td>\t\t\t<td>(i)</td>\t\t\t<td><img height=\"81\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/9c20e707-adca-4cce-9b67-da8a04843e33-image.png\" width=\"86\" /></td>\t\t</tr>\t\t<tr>\t\t\t<td>(b)</td>\t\t\t<td>Neoprene</td>\t\t\t<td>(ii)</td>\t\t\t<td><img height=\"91\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/e6207049-2b51-4140-824c-b1de64ec7bbc-image.png\" width=\"132\" /></td>\t\t</tr>\t\t<tr>\t\t\t<td>(c)</td>\t\t\t<td>Acrylonitrile</td>\t\t\t<td>(iii)</td>\t\t\t<td><img height=\"30\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/10d351ed-af28-4dc4-ac37-c8e1d1ad3b12-image.png\" width=\"116\" /></td>\t\t</tr>\t\t<tr>\t\t\t<td>(d)</td>\t\t\t<td>Isoprene</td>\t\t\t<td>(iv)</td>\t\t\t<td><img height=\"57\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/9945c978-7605-4857-9661-3c32f2d37161-image.png\" width=\"89\" /></td>\t\t</tr>\t</tbody></table>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (22 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":31201,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["Polyester","Bakelite","Nylon-&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>6</mn></math>","Melamine"],"answer":1,"solution":"Novolac on heating with formaldehyde undergoes cross-linking to form an infusible solid mass called Bakelite.&nbsp;It is a thermosetting polymer that cannot be reused or remoulded.&nbsp;&nbsp;Bakelite is used for making combs, phonograph records, electrical switches, and handles of various utensils","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (26 Aug Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":31240,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["Nylon -6,6","Bakelite","Buna - N","Teflon"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p>Thermosetting polymer :A thermosetting polymer can be moulded into desired shape when hot, but once these get cooled and hardened, they cannot be remoulded again. An example of this is&nbsp;Bakelite.</p><p>&nbsp;</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2014 (19 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":31179,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>III</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>II</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>IV</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>III</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>IV</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>II</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>III</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>IV</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>II</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>III</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>IV</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>II</mi></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p>(A) Glyptal polymer is used as a manufacture of paints and Lacquers</p><p>(B) Neoprene is formed by the free radical polymerisation of chloroprene. It is used for manufacturing conveyor belts, gaskets and hoses.</p><p>(C)&nbsp;Polyacrylonitrile is used as a substitute for wool in making commercial fibres as orlon or acrilan.</p><p>(D)&nbsp;Low density polythene (LDP) is chemically inert and tough but flexible and a poor conductor of electricity. Hence, it is used&nbsp;in the insulation of electricity carrying wires and manufacture of squeeze bottles, toys and flexible pipes.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (25 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":31245,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["Acetal","$\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{CHO}$","$\\mathrm{HCHO}$","Chlorobenzene"],"answer":2,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/_HP4PJOHPGaNw3jnAzv_PrSjcvp-3ialmPa8C8Bwrxo.original.fullsize.png\"><br><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/ZzNnOyw0wnc8tcpeT1pHzup4MWAn_-lds8r1CZ-zBmo.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2013 (25 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":31236,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["Its synthesis required dioxygen or a peroxide initiator as a catalyst","It is used in the manufacture of buckets, dust - bins etc.","Its synthesis requires high pressure","It is a poor conductor of electricity"],"answer":1,"solution":"Low density polythene: It is obtained by the polymerization of ethene high pressure of 1000-2000 atm. at a temp. of 350 K to 570 K in the pressure of traces of dioxygen or a peroxide initiator (cont).<br /><br />Low density polythene is chemically inert and poor conductor of electricity. It is used for manufacture squeeze bottles, toys and flexible pipes.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2016 (03 Apr)","image":null},{"id":31232,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["<p><img height=\"86\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/6cea7244-5210-48d8-82a9-e4dcc95af70e-image.png\" style=\"float: left;\" width=\"304\" /></p>","<p><img height=\"55\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/612676f0-8b71-49ae-887c-435530dc2063-image.png\" width=\"258\" /></p>","<p><img height=\"64\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/874d223d-341e-4744-ac82-db6619f64de8-image.png\" style=\"float: left;\" width=\"288\" /></p>","<p><img height=\"65\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/04e0a3fa-3c22-416d-9f11-325a78433146-image.png\" style=\"float: left;\" width=\"189\" /></p>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p><img height=\"73\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/950a85bc-36c7-4cda-a925-3b5e656eabbd-image.png\" width=\"382\" /></p><p><br />Nylon<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo></math>Nylon<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn></math><br />Polymer of glycine and amino caproic acid.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2017 (09 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":31214,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["Nylon 6, 6","Buna &ndash; N","Bakelite","Nylon 6"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p><img height=\"256\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/c460ebbe-546c-4fa1-8b09-72bb7f5ab5cd-image.png\" width=\"517\" /></p><p>The&nbsp;polymers&nbsp;made by&nbsp;addition polymerisation&nbsp;from two different monomers are termed as copolymers, e.g.,&nbsp;Buna-S,&nbsp;Buna-N, etc.</p><p>Bakelite&nbsp;is a&nbsp;condensation polymer&nbsp;of formaldehyde and phenol . In practice, the phenol and formaldehyde are first polymerized to a small extent by using the proper choice of catalyst and temperature.</p><p>Nylon is also condensation polymer.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (05 Sep Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":31239,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["Poly vinyl chloride","Bakelite","Glyptal","Polypropene"],"answer":2,"solution":"Glyptal is polymer of glycerol and phthalic anhydride.<br /><br /><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/Jee_1_Quest_5_soln.jpg\" style=\"width: 346px; height: 182px;\" />","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2015 (04 Apr)","image":null},{"id":31251,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["Styrene and vinyl chloride","Acrylonitrile and vinyl chloride","Adipic acid and ethylene glycol","Phenol and formaldehyde"],"answer":3,"solution":"Phenol and formaldehyde undergo condensation polymerisation under two different conditions to give a cross linked polymer called bakelite.\n<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/ks9XxfbvjxwiPOcrYoHy9JsdYiizifITqLkpIjZmMF8.original.fullsize.png\"><br><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/uVwmwKbUyVqjPk6L36TrZxVER7s3h51nJQZTyB1f88o.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2012 (12 May Online)","image":null},{"id":31220,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["Nylon <math><mn>6</mn><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mn>6</mn></math>","Neoprene","Buna<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi></math>","Teflon"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>In the condensation polymerization reaction, the elimination of small molecules such as water,&nbsp;alcohol, hydrogen chloride takes&nbsp;place.</p><p>Nylon,&nbsp;a condensation polymer, is made of hexamethylene diamine and adipic acid.</p><p>Buna<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi></math>, Teflon&nbsp;and Neoprene are addition polymers.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/8468db6d-1872-41fd-9e75-3d191663fed2-image.png\" style=\"width: 379px; height: 336px;\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (10 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":31218,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["Bakelite","PVC","Nylon 6","Buna-N"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Thermosetting polymers are cross-linked or heavily branched molecules, which on heating undergo extensive cross linking and cannot be reused. Bakelite is a thermosetting polymer<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/830222da-c00d-4577-91d5-10925ec9ef9b-image.png\" style=\"width: 360px; height: 161px;\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (12 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":31200,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/11437bc0-0573-403b-8769-e4b21235a221-image.png\" style=\"width: 302px; height: 147px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/0cd826b6-0b9b-4a94-b9d2-55057db129b5-image.png\" style=\"width: 331px; height: 105px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/efa6ed8d-64e1-4cf5-a485-4b8d02c58a9d-image.png\" style=\"width: 307px; height: 179px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/7b88d72c-d917-4cb3-996a-252409f1ec66-c4be2062-0275-40c2-a396-e028d0933f0a-image.png\" style=\"width: 285px; height: 155px;\" />"],"answer":2,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/8eccdccb-e62e-4927-83e3-17e9b1b798a0-image.png\" style=\"width: 831px; height: 358px;\" />","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (31 Aug Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":31208,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/e8b333d0-2e9b-41b2-bb82-ae570c27d5e7-image.png\" style=\"width: 191px; height: 85px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/0e1937d4-dab3-4bb9-87d7-f4d4c396e7f2-image.png\" style=\"width: 432px; height: 85px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/cfd57551-9663-45f4-b6c9-d5c0d6521f37-image.png\" style=\"width: 298px; height: 71px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/6eb9725f-9368-46ea-97b0-2f4b9c9f3a47-image.png\" style=\"width: 275px; height: 152px;\" />"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p>The structure of&nbsp; the neoprene polymer is as shown below.<br />It is obtained from chloroprene which is&nbsp;2-chloro buta-1,3-diene. It is an addition homopolymer with rubber like structure and properties.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/87f57410-e1e1-429b-b7ff-058a72574957-image.png\" style=\"width: 395px; height: 238px;\" /></p><p>Neoprene is a polymer of chloroprene which is chemically 2- chlorobuta - 1, 3 -diene (isoprene).&nbsp;Neoprene exhibits good chemical stability and maintains flexibility over a wide temperature range.</p><p>&nbsp;</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (26 Feb Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":31209,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["Synthesis of Buna-<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi></math>&nbsp;needs nascent oxygen.","Buna-<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi></math>&nbsp;is a synthetic and linear thermosetting polymer.","Buna-<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></math>&nbsp;is a natural polymer.","Neoprene is an addition copolymer used in plastic bucket manufacturing."],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Buna-S is an elastomer<br /><br />Buna-N is a synthetic polymer<br /><br />Buna-S is polymerised by addition polymerisation method which needs radical initiator for chain propagation step. Nascent oxygen can be used as an Radical initiator.<br /><br />Neoprene is a synthetic rubber.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/a90f48a4-6bdd-46de-98a1-3b0bfe008507-image.png\" style=\"width: 476px; height: 101px;\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (25 Feb Shift 1)","image":null}]